Stomper the pony has fled into the western Wildwood.\n\nYou should look for signs of Stomper's flight.
'Poor Stomper! He must be so scared! Please, find him!'
'Oh happy day! You found my supplies. Oh dear, but where is poor Stomper? Do you see any sign of him? Oh dear, oh dear, oh dear!'
These tracks look fresh! He's nearby!
Minda is in the western Wildwood.\n\nYou should talk to Minda Heathertoes.

'Stomper! You did it, [placeholder]!\n\n'Oh, but my waggon! My beautiful waggon! Completely ruined! Well, I suppose I must be grateful for what I yet have. Thank you, [placeholder]! Come, let us leave this place, lest more brigands or Wargs come seeking their friends. I heard there is a pond nearby, and Stomper looks like he could use a drink. I shall meet you there!'
After escaping from the wicked waggon snatcher, Stomper the Pony has fled, but he may be charging into even greater danger!
Hoof-prints, but also very large paw-prints
Hoof-prints may be found in the Wildwood.\n\nYou should look for more prints from Stomper the pony.
Wildwood pony-stalkers can be found in Wildwood.\n\nMinda Heathertoes has asked you to defeat the Wargs hunting Stomper the pony.
Minda can be found near a pond in the central Wildwood.\n\nYou should talk to Minda Heathertoes.
These tracks look fresh! He's nearby!

'Thank you for meeting me here, friend. I know I have asked much of you, but you were the only one who would help me! I am so very grateful.

'I imagine you are probably wondering what a hobbit such as myself is doing so far from home. I have the honour of being apprenticed to the master chef, Lyn Woodsorrel. She sent me forth into the Wildwood to collect ingredients for the first ever Feast of the Wildwood.

'But, alas! You know how that went. I am so grateful for all the help you've given me, and am loath to ask for more... but ask I shall! I desperately need your help gathering ingredients, or the feast will be ruined! I will be ruined!'
Hoof-prints may be found in the Wildwood.\n\nYou should look for more prints from Stomper the pony.

DNT - 
Stomper the pony is lost in the Wildwoods. 

Rescue Stomper the pony from the Wargs!
Minda can be found in the western Wildwood.\n\nYou should talk to Minda Heathertoes.
